For a configuration ${\sf Q}({\bf r})$, the requirement Eq.~(\ref{tensorial}) is however not the complete story --- it is a necessary but, in general, not the only condition the tensorial configuration must satisfy. 
Namely, the tensorial constraint Eq.~(\ref{tensorial}) does not include the effect of chain rigidity and therefore requires the backup of the tighter vectorial constraint Eq.~(\ref{vectorial}) as we will propose. In what follows, we will show that 



